@document.meta
title: Configuration
description: Plugin configuration reference
@end

* Configuration

  The plugin accepts a `NorgPluginOptions` object.

** mode

   @code typescript
   type mode = 'svelte' | 'vue' | 'react' | 'html' | 'metadata';
   @end

   - `svelte` — generates Svelte components
   - `vue` — generates Vue SFCs
   - `react` — generates JSX components
   - `html` — generates raw HTML strings
   - `metadata` — exports only metadata and TOC

** arboriumConfig

   Configure syntax highlighting for code blocks:

   @code typescript
   // Single theme
   arboriumConfig: { theme: 'github-dark' }

   // Light/dark theme pair
   arboriumConfig: {
     themes: { light: 'github-light', dark: 'github-dark' }
   }
   @end

   Import the generated CSS with:

   @code typescript
   import 'virtual:norg-arborium.css';
   @end

** componentDir

   Path to a directory of framework components:

   @code typescript
   norgPlugin({
     mode: 'vue',
     componentDir: './src/components'
   })
   @end

** components

   Explicitly map component names to import paths:

   @code typescript
   norgPlugin({
     mode: 'vue',
     components: {
       Counter: './src/components/Counter.vue'
     }
   })
   @end

** Full Example

   @code typescript
   import { norgPlugin } from 'vite-plugin-norg';

   norgPlugin({
     mode: 'vue',
     arboriumConfig: { theme: 'github-dark' },
     componentDir: './src/components',
     components: {
       SpecialWidget: './src/lib/SpecialWidget.vue'
     }
   });
   @end
